### 8. GENERATE() PATTERN FOR TEXT GENERATION TASKS

**TextGenerationPipeline Example (lines 984-1080):**
```javascript
export class TextGenerationPipeline extends Pipeline {
  async _call(texts, generate_kwargs = {}) {
    // Tokenize input
    const text_inputs = this.tokenizer(inputs, {
      add_special_tokens,
      padding: true,
      truncation: true,
    });

    // Call model.generate() with merged kwargs
    const outputTokenIds = await this.model.generate({
      ...text_inputs,
      ...generate_kwargs
    });

    // Decode output
    const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(outputTokenIds, {
      skip_special_tokens: true,
    });

    return toReturn;
  }
}
```

**DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline Example (lines 2732-2779):**
