# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

Transformers.js already has `AutoModelForImageTextToText` defined in `src/models.js` (line 8736), supporting 11 vision-language models (LLaVA, SmolVLM, PaliGemma, Qwen2-VL, Florence2, etc.). However, there is no corresponding pipeline class or task registration for this model type. This plan adds the missing pipeline layer so users can call `pipeline('image-text-to-text', ...)` to run inference on any of these multimodal models.

The task is pure addition — no existing classes or behaviours are modified.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `src/pipelines.js` | All pipeline classes + `SUPPORTED_TASKS` registration + `pipeline()` factory |
| `src/models.js` | `AutoModelForImageTextToText` at line 8736 (already exists, read-only) |
| `tests/pipelines/test_pipelines_image_text_to_text.js` | New test file (auto-discovered by `collect_and_execute_pipeline_tests`) |

---

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` import in `src/pipelines.js`

**Location:** lines 16–45 (existing `import { … } from './models.js'` block)

Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the existing import list:

```js
import {
    // ... existing imports ...
    AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,
    AutoModelForImageTextToText,   // ← add this
    PreTrainedModel,
} from './models.js';
```

---

### Step 2 — Add JSDoc typedefs for `ImageTextToTextPipeline` in `src/pipelines.js`

**Location:** After line 2005 (end of `ImageToTextPipeline` class), before `ImageClassificationPipeline`.

Pattern: mirrors `ImageToTextSingle` / `ImageToTextPipelineType` at lines 1943–1953.

```js
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Process an image and text prompt, generating text output.
 * @param {ImageInput} image The image input.
 * @param {string} text The text prompt.
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments passed to the model's generate method.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput>} An array of objects containing the generated text.
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */
```

---

### Step 3 — Add `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class in `src/pipelines.js`

**Location:** Immediately after the typedefs from Step 2.

Design decisions:
- Takes a **single image** + **single text prompt** (same approach as `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline`).
- Calls `this.processor(preparedImage, text)` — image first, text second — matching the dominant convention used by LLaVA, PaliGemma, SmolVLM processors.
- Uses character-based prompt-stripping (same technique as `TextGenerationPipeline` lines 1053–1067) to strip the echoed input from the decoder-only model output.

```js
/**
 * Image-text-to-text pipeline using `AutoModelForImageTextToText`. This pipeline
 * accepts an image and a text prompt, and returns generated text.
 *
 * **Example:** Generate a response from an image and a prompt w/ `HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct`.
 * ```javascript
 * const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct');
 * const image = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg';
 * const output = await pipe(image, 'What is in the image?');
 * // [{ generated_text: 'Two cats are sitting on a couch.' }]
 * ```
 */
export class ImageTextToTextPipeline extends (/** @type {new (options: TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs) => ImageTextToTextPipelineType} */ (Pipeline)) {

    /**
     * Create a new ImageTextToTextPipeline.
     * @param {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs} options An object used to instantiate the pipeline.
     */
    constructor(options) {
        super(options);
    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(image, text, generate_kwargs = {}) {
        // NOTE: For now, we only support a batch size of 1
        const preparedImage = (await prepareImages(image))[0];

        // Process image and text jointly through the model's processor
        const inputs = await this.processor(preparedImage, text);

        // Generate output token ids
        const outputTokenIds = /** @type {Tensor} */(await this.model.generate({
            ...inputs,
            ...generate_kwargs,
        }));

        // Decode both full output and original prompt (skip image special tokens)
        const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(outputTokenIds, {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        });
        const promptLengths = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(inputs.input_ids, {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        }).map(x => x.length);

        // Strip echoed input from generated output
        return decoded.map((text, i) => ({
            generated_text: text.slice(promptLengths[i]).trim(),
        }));
    }
}
```

---

### Step 4 — Register in `SUPPORTED_TASKS` in `src/pipelines.js`

**Location:** After the `"image-to-text"` entry (lines 3244–3255), before `"image-classification"`.

Reuse existing classes:
- `AutoTokenizer` (already imported, line 17)
- `AutoProcessor` (already imported, line 47)
- `AutoModelForImageTextToText` (new import added in Step 1)

